snippet.textDisplay:
This is just a drawn-out rambling over a few chords. Sorry, but I wouldnt say it's groundbreaking or even very interesting. I guess he really doesnt have to try to please anyone anymore, but why advertise this as something it's not?

He's beating a dead horse with a limp fist here. No real production/mix value to be found, and very vague/undetermined, very very niche songwriting value.. He has released much better material before, and I justifiably compare whatever the hell this is to his greatest with disgust..

snippet.textDisplay: Thank you Mr. Dylan. Tried to answer with the others, but must be a 500 maximum. Couldn’t leave without thanking you and commenting on such a meaningful tribute, to me personally. The day President Kennedy was murdered is my first memory in life, which seems impossible. I wasn’t born until November 1961, yet remember the panic and pain in my mother of what was happening on our B&W tv. I didn’t understand, but she was in such pain that I screamed and cried with her! She put me on a blanket on the floor where I looked at the tv to see what upset her so. They kept showing it, so yes I remember seeing it. I didn’t comprehend at the time he’d never live again in this world, but knew it was very bad by everyone’s reactions, especially that of my mother who adored him. She phoned my oldest sister to come right away, whom I was glad to see. Today, my talented grandson hasn’t woke bc we were up until 4:00 AM having a sleepover. Only of my only son, Dylan is a very multi talented, gifted guitar player singer/song writer. Yes, he’s your namesake, as his Dad grew up on your music, as I feel his children will. He’s only 14, yet with the help of his art teacher, another talented musician, started a rock band at his middle school. They did so well first concert after the school band, the board approved a grant for them for instruments making it official. Their middle school now has a rock band as an elective option for the children named School of Rock. He buys guitars with every bit of money he earns of course lol. But the school provided a couple, a set of drums and a keyboard. More materials too I’m sure. His last year there, now out due to Corona. Had just become social instead of shy. I’m sure you understand, if you ever read these things. Hopefully someone will who can relate. Stay safe, as it’s all dangerous now in many ways. Our generation is taking a bad hit, so may God have mercy on us all. Don’t think we (baby boomers) will get the prevention if and when available. Please stay safe and care for yourself. Thank you for a lifetime of beautiful music.

My Poem To Bob Dylan. By Veronica Harris

Martin Luther and Malcom X would agree. about The CIA killing spree The King was taken down the same way. Maybe it took you 56 years to have your say, I am sure it has been in your poetic mind for that long. 56 years to release this Amazing song. They should have released The Truth in Twenty Seventeen Saying something for something not seen. But we are all still living in a dream. Rump stopped it. Homicidal Ego Maniacs rule the World. The truth will never be "Officially" told. It takes no idiot to see the lies that are sown But we all know, every single person we own. "Power" is paid off. Just depends if you laugh or you cough The guilt comes with so many masks Who will tell the truth when asked Freedom in a child Freedom in a whore Where did they tell us to stall 56 years of hell on this earth. Don't tell me that I am the last man To Feel Thirst. Damocles sword held above me So high. All we had left was a massive sigh. Poem By Veronica Harris ///////////////////////////////////// Even our Freedom means nothing. Truth is the Prisoner of Liars. I shared this song every where Bob, as I am sure all your Fans have. Stay Strong. Stay alive X

snippet.textDisplay:
I was 11 when I heard the awful news while sitting in the backseat of the family care. Hysteria was my reaction. I loved this guy so much; a Hero.

Mom opened the rear car door and pulled out of the backseat: "What the hell is wrong with you?"!!

She could not ever understand.how I felt about the heroes in my heart. Losing one after another of tje prophets had a sort of crushing numbing effect it took me years to get over.

I are people posting things like, "Our govt isn't working for the people now.,"

"This problem is not new," I posted. "Recall, JFK, RFK, MLK, John, and, on down the list....."


She could not ever understand how I felt about the heroes in my heart. Losing one after another of the prophets had a sort of crushing numbing effect it took me years to get over.

I see people posting things like, "Our government isn't working for the people now.,"

"This is not new," I posted. "Recall, JFK, RFK, MLK, John, and, on down the list....."

I love you as real family Mr. Bob Dylan - one who feels like I do. I have been lucky to see you in concert several times; most recently at Red Rocks 7.3016.


Hearing you now has inspired me to carry through with Uploading my YT Channel today.


I love you and know you are well

Thank you so very much for everything kindred soul. You are The Master Spiritual Explorer and I deeply appreciate your courage. Example.


love you asI real family Mr. Bob Dylan - one who feels like I do🐦💜🌿

“In JFK and the Unspeakable Jim Douglass has
distilled all the best available research into a very
well-documented and convincing portrait of
President Kennedy's transforming turn to peace, at
the cost of his life. Personally, it has made a very
big impact on me. After reading it in Dallas, I was
moved for the first time to visit Dealey Plaza.
I URGE ALL AMERICANS TO READ THIS BOOK
and come to their own conclusions about why he
died and why — after fifty years — it still matters.”
— Robert F. Kennedy, Jr.

snippet.textDisplay:
My Poem To Bob Dylan. By Veronica Harris


Martin Luther and Malcom X would agree.

about The CIA killing spree

The King was taken down the same way.

Maybe it took you 56 years

to have your say

I am sure it has been in your poetic mind for that long.

56 years to release this Amazing song

They should have released

The Truth
in Twenty Seventeen
Saying something for something not seen
But we are all still living in a dream.

Rump stopped it.

Homicidal Ego Maniacs rule the World.

The truth will never be
"Officially" told.

It takes no idiot to see the lies that are sown

But we all know, every single person we own.

"Power" is paid off.

Just depends if you laugh or you cough
The guilt comes with so many masks

Who will tell the truth when asked ?

Freedom in a child
Freedom in a whore

Where did they tell us to stall
56 years of hell on this earth.

Don't tell me that I am the last man

To Feel Thirst

Damocles Sword held above me
So High
All we had left

was a Massive Sigh.


Poem By Veronica Harris

/////////////////////////////////////





Even our Freedom means nothing.
Truth is the Prisoner of Liars.
I shared this song every where Bob, as I am sure all your Fans have. Stay Strong. Stay alive X

Peace and blessing to you and yours. Merci.
